race.comment: Onto an open Tatura Cup. SO RISQUE (4) has been well beaten his past couple but they've been in strong races, the latest in a very fast BM90 at Flemington behind Persian Spirit who went like a rocket. This is easier, and going back three runs he's finished second to the Group class King Zephyr which would win this. GEORGIE GET MAD (10) ran a good race fresh at Kyneton over 1203m and will be fitter for it. He draws the pole and will hunt up here to land close to the speed out to a more suitable trip. PORTER (8) continues to race well and looks to set up nicely here. He comes back slightly in trip but the 1450m looks ideal for him and he'll tag a good speed. BLACK STORM (5) resumes. His best form reads well for this and he's won a jumpout leading in. INDISPENSABLE (1) should be fitter for two solid runs.
